	Berry Vogue    
	London, June 12 (PTI): Actress Halle Berry will become the first black woman to grace fashion bible Vogues all-important September isue.       
	The issue is the most important of the year as it showcases the autumn/winter trends, and brings in the maximum revenue for Vogue with most pages of advertising.      
	 The magazines decision to put Berry, 41, on the cover has been hailed as a landmark, repors the Daily Mail. Beverly Johnson was the first black woman on a Vogue cover in 1974 and was followed by Naomi Campbell and athlete Marion Jones.    
	Zeta Queen    
	London: Some of Britains best-loved television personalities have been recognised in the Queens Birthday Honours, in a list led by Catherine Zeta Jones, reports The Daily Telegraph. The Welsh actress, awarded a CBE, is now a member of a Hollywood dynasty but her rise to fame began in the gentle Sunday evening comedy, The Darling Buds of May. She is joined in the list by three legends of Coronation Street.                                                                                                                                                      
